<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barlow</persName>,
                                    United States marshal, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>, Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-06-28"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 28, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p>The tugs are at Gardner’s Point, on Long Island, opposite New London,
                                waiting for the Catharine Whiting. Will you telegraph at once to the
                                United States revenue-cutter at New London to obey my orders? I want
                                to send her over to detain the tugs. Please answer.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>FRANCIS C. BARLOW.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>